items.text: 天天来 fried hokkien noodles best around central. 88 粥品 stall offers great silky smooth congee w a stick of fried fritter.
Try the daily come Hokkien mee, chey Sua carrot cake and fish soup (#02-08)
Fishball noodles. 135 Fishball Noodle #02-11 may hv lots of newspaper mentions but I find his fishballs too firm/hard for my liking
Recommended for Mackerel Fish Soups, especially Set A. @ Stall #02-08. Fresh and Best.
Supreme pork chop ! Must try
The 02-19 stall is taken up but dunno what they are selling
Teochew handmade pau is 60 cents per piece. The porridge is also good!
Chey Sua carrot cake is SHEN!!!
金花源肉干
The tian tian lai fried prawn noodles is simply fantastic. Must try.
The teochew handmade Pau stall sells nice mini braised pork belly pau... Power.
Uggli Muffins! luv their banana walnut baby muffins! best!
天天来炒福建面，check it out
The carrot cake is the best! Crunchy texture and stands out from the rest. An original of the original!
02-33 127(一巷)鱼粥.鱼汤.海鲜汤 好吃又经济
Plenty of gd food here, but pls spread the word by mouth instead of appear on TV, the hokkien mee appeared on 抢摊大行动collapse eventually after the failure to cope with public demand
The economic bee hoon, Nasi Lemak stall is really good. Long queue expected. Near bak kwa and muffin stall.
Most stalls have there for 20 yrs & more. Bak Chor mee,  Fishball noodles, Fish porridge, Vegetarian, etc etc. It's a place for good food at down-to-earth prices!
Stall #02-07: Tian Tian Lai (Come Daily) Fried Hokkien Prawn Mee [MUST ORDER!]
Best carrot cake 青山, best teochew bao
#02-02 潮洲自制饱点 Teochew Handmade Pau - 小肉包，叉烧包，糯米鸡 are my favourite
Today happen to be there to buy their cookies. Went there only realize not enough money, the owner asked me to return him next time I see him. Good service 10/10
Market opp PHILIPS got some very tasty fried bee hoon...lots of lard, yummy!
Market is reopened earlier than expected! However not all stalls are opened yet.
#02-30 青山菜头棵 Chey Sua Carrot Cake - the best carrot cake in Singapore
what makes or breaks for me for fish soup besides no 'xingwei' is the chilli and the soup. 02-08's fish soup was quite enjoyable.
Tasty fish soup
The 127 lorong 1 fish porridge / soup stall is good. must try. a bit salty though.
Plenty of good food here.. But hope dun appear on tv rather than spread d gd of them by word of mouth
Chet sua carrot cake freaking power. MUST try
Powerful Chey sua carrot cake
Only 20%-25% of stalls are open on Monday mornings 😔
carrot cake at 02-30 carrpt cake
nasi Kemak chicken Wing is good. must add on: sotong 片! beside the muffin stall.
tian tian lai hokkien prawn mee...
天天来fried prawn mee. Must try! But waiting time at least 30mins
Airy design. Good for typical local heartland breakfast. Carrot cake and kopi kow are the highlights.
Chey Sua Carrot Cake here is highly recommended! Most delicious carrot cake I've ever tried. Bet you'll be back for more :)
Need western food stall serves decent pork chops and cutlets
The vegetarian stall #02-07 serve the best vegetarian food lah! Must try!
The kway chap here is nice! :D #02-14
Joo Heng wanton mee: the best!
Try the kway chap here! It's nice! You can choose between nyo hiang, pigs intestine and qiam chai! My fav is nyo hiang. Hmmm..yum! Stall: 大成棵汁, #02-14
Must try the hokkien prawn mee by tian tian lai.
Other than Chey Sua white chay tow kueh, don't miss one of the best fried hokkien prawn noodles in town - Tian Tian Lai!
The fried hokkein mee is great! :)
Best carrot cake, Chey Sua carrot cake. Nice hokkien prawn mee, 天天来
Looks desolate at 5pm on a Saturday; most stalls were closed. You should definitely come early.
Stall unit 02-18 & 19 are vacant for interested party to take over
Prawn mee. Worth your wait, worth your money and worth your chewing. Just go by 1 pm or else it might be sold out
Try the mee Siam! It's not spicy!
makansutra recommends come daily hokkien mee; pretty good but chockful of lard
If u like wanton mee, try Maggie's wanton noodles at Blk 126 coffeeshop
Like the dimsum
Forget to mention it's Chey Sua carrot cake stall no 02-30
Porridge is nice, must try.
Come daily hokkien mee!!!!
The teochew handmade pau has really mini versions of their paus!
Good food here : chey Shah carrot cake, porridge, tea from the stall near to the carrot cake stall
The Teochew pau really got stupid attitude problem! Should try the congee @ #02-29...
The lemon sauce chicken chop next to the Hokkien Mee is quite unique.
Food stalls with great food & value for money
Good porridge :)
02-19 left vacate again after the duck rice closed just few days into business .. Tough
Supreme Pork Chop Rice (一品排骨）is now available at Blk 127 Lorong 1 #02-19.  Used to be only available in Middle Road, now you can also enjoy it if you are in Toa Payoh.
88粥品 must try ! Fresh and nice
#02-08 fish soup is nice! Try their crab bee hoon. Superb!
The vegetarian stall at 02-18 will be relocated to 02-36 from aug10
Da Cheng kway chap! #02-14! Buy individual set if you are instead of telling them for 2(or more person) cos individual serving seems to have larger quantity!
Must try #02-08 fish soup. No MSG! Thus very healthy. Tasty and I love here!!!!!!! Aunty and uncle also super nice.
Mini kong ba bao from bao stall is a good snack
rose nasi padang @blk 125.unbeatable.
Must try Teow Chew handmade bao (order 1 each or a dozen) (#02-2) and Fried hokkien mee (#02-27)
"western food" 02-25 has great western food. Must try! Fish n chips are very good!
the happy family pasta has the best Linguini Seafood Marinara! Do try! (:
The fish soup #02-33 is good!
pwah!!! kopi o kosong only for 50cts!!!
Try Henry's Hainanese Chicken Rice :D Tender chicken and very aromatic rice ! ^^
Vegetarian options: specialised stall, soya beancurd, yutiao, baos, rice with vege, local desserts, chai tow kway (fried carrot cake), muffins, yong tau foo, prata, thosai, peanut porridge, more
The fried prawn hokkien mee stall is closed at 6pm.
Wantan mee. Joo Heng 02-12. Noodles had bitter aftertaste. Their wantan filling recipe uses a lot of pepper. Char siew cooked with an portable electric oven, lacking the smokiness
Deanna's Kitchen halal prawn noodles - as good as the Chinese version! Rich broth with depth and big juicy prawns. 😋🍜🦐
